text: too many good talks to pick between :disappointed:

>Developing Mobile Experiences at Facebook's scale
This is a must see :troll:
it's tempting just to see what they have to say haha
the Lint talk in the same timeslot might be good though
ya, i’m curious about the lint talk. i definitely don’t utilize it enough
i actually _have_ wanted to write my own lint checks but never looked into it
it’s the thought that counts, right?
when people say ‘scale’ in regards to development I often find it hard to think of them as anything other than an idiot
I thought facebooks idea of scaling is “fuck it ship it” and “who cares about bugs”
their philosophy is basically if the end result is an objectively better product then the code underneath doesn't matter
but then they have talks scheduled from people talking about performance
> Building beautiful & performant user interfaces - Kevin Jung Instagram
> Understanding Performance In The Wild - Delyan Kratunov Facebook Inc.
well their engineering tooling team’s work far more interesting than their application team’s work
yet the code is similarly sloppy, at least by reputation (e.g. fresco)
i actually haven't used any of their tools except stetho briefly so can't really speak from experience
